en texts about the experience of the Hajj) and Hajj practices of Bosnian Muslims. It redefines the ways pilgrimage can be understood and offers new methods for investigating the meaning and importance of Hajj for generations of premodern and modern believers. It also throws light on Balkan communities previously ignored by modern scholarship in Islamic, religious, and area studies. Breaking with the predominant academic trends of focusing on nationalism and ethnic conflict in the region, it instead puts the spotlight on the richness of texts, and visual and archival material, and focuses on genres that challenge the established literary canons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aBosnian literaturexMuslim authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aIslamzBosnia and HerzegovinaxHistoryxSources. 0aIslamic literaturezBosnia and HerzegovinaxHistory and criticism. 0aIslamic storiesxHistory. 0aMuslim pilgrims and pilgrimageszSaudi ArabiazMeccaxIn literature. 0aMuslim pilgrims and pilgrimageszSaudi ArabiazMecca. 0aMuslimszBosnia and HerzegovinavBiography. 0aMuslimszBosnia and HerzegovinaxHistory. 0aTravel writerszBosnia and HerzegovinavBiography. 0aTravel writingzBosnia and HerzegovinaxHistory. 4aIslamic Studies. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079764040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147449413740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474494137423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474494137/original  a978-3-11-079764-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5